# GRIND-TOTAL equivalents for mutative_verbs.py — see
# tests/evals/evidence/equivalents-security-core.md, Categories M*.
# Each entry is a mutant proven GENUINELY EQUIVALENT: no honest input
# distinguishes it from the original for ANY reachable input. Excluded from the
# kill-rate denominator. Killable siblings are killed by tests in
# tests/hooks/modules/security/test_mutative_verbs.py and
# tests/hooks/modules/security/test_mutative_verbs_mutants.py.
#
# IDENTITY FORMAT (re-init-proof): each entry is the mutant's STABLE identity
#   operator_name|start_row:start_col-end_row:end_col|occurrence
# NOT a job_id (cosmic-ray regenerates job_ids on every `init`; a job_id-keyed
# skip silently matches nothing after re-init -- the false-100% trap). The
# harness (mutkill_approval_grants.py: stable_id / compute_skip_jobids) resolves
# these to the current session and WARNS on any unmatched token. Re-keyed
# against mutative-verbs.sqlite (822 specs, post-desacople HEAD).
#
# Endpoint: 747 killed by tests, 75 equivalents below; 0 untriaged survivors
# (confirmed via mutkill --skip-file).
#
# ===========================================================================
# M1 — import-fallback `except ImportError` handlers (3). The sibling modules
# always import in-process, so the except body is unreachable.
